rComments: Just a very entertaining class and a very encouraging prof. You can never go wrong by taking a Pascale class I can tell you that!!!
One of the favourite profs I ever had. The class content was great and it's hard to get bored in this class. It really helps that the prof is super down to earth.

The course he gave was very informative and well organized. He obviously cares a lot about his students and makes sure to make everything clear so that there are no misunderstandings. Also, he is very responsive to emails, so if you have any concerns, youll have a quick response. Would recommend him 100%.

Very approachable, wants students to do well. Small group size for projects, and marks generously, especially if presenting early. I enjoyed the projects, and I almost always hate groupwork. Prepares reading summaries - VERY useful, closely reflect quizzes and exams. Cannot overstate value of summaries. Has Québecois accent, but easily understood.
Great prof, highly recommend. Very inspiration lectures and I learnt a lot.

If you want an easy A, take his class. If you genuinely want to learn and come out of his class smarter than you went in, dont. His easy marking scheme is laughable, half-assed assignments get As, reading his power points and textbook ch summaries are all you need. No one is going to complain bout easy As. But his class was pure common sense.

BEST. PROF. EVER. He is such an understanding prof and really really cares for his students. Alway gives fair marks for your hard work, and if you disagree he really tries understand your point of view and improve. If you are doing your readings for your exams, handing everything on time.. then A+ . UofO really needs profs like him.
